==Trivia==
*In the comics, Hank Pym is one of the founding members of the [[Avengers]], and the creator of [[Ultron]]. Later, he became known as '''Yellowjacket''' before he passed the Ant-Man mantle to [[Scott Lang]].
**In later comics, Pym is a member of the [[Illuminati]], a group made of the smartest and most powerful characters in the Marvel Universe, including [[Black Bolt]], [[Tony Stark]], [[Bruce Banner]], [[Medusa]], [[Stephen Strange]] and [[T'Challa]].

==Behind the Scenes==
*Originally, Hank Pym was mentioned by name in ''[[Thor (film)|Thor]]'' when [[Erik Selvig]] tells [[Jane Foster]] about his contacts in [[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] This was cut because the filmmakers thought that it was too soon to mention him.
*[[Nathan Fillion]] was in the running to play Pym before it was decided the character would not appear in ''[[The Avengers]]'' and never auditioned.
*Before Michael Douglas was cast as Hank Pym, {{WPS|Sean Bean}}, {{WPS|Pierce Brosnan}} and {{WPS|Gary Oldman}} were considered for the part.
*[[Michael Douglas]]' appearance in ''{{WPS|Wall Street (1987 film)|Wall Street}}'' was the primary reference for Hank Pym's youthful appearance in flashbacks.<ref>[https://www.fxguide.com/featured/a-bugs-wife-ant-man-and-the-wasp/ A Bug’s Wife: Ant-Man and the Wasp]</ref>
*While developing the story of ''[[Avengers: Endgame]]'', [[Christopher Markus]] and [[Stephen McFeely]] considered having Hank and [[Janet van Dyne]] appearing with their [[Ant-Man Suit]]s during the [[Battle of Earth]] sequence, but they ultimately scrapped them from the battle to not make it a "character orgy."<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2019/04/29/movies/avengers-endgame-questions-and-answers.html ‘Avengers: Endgame’: The Screenwriters Answer Every Question You Might Have]</ref>
*According to [[Jeff Loveness]], Hank Pym was originally going to die in ''[[Ant-Man and the Wasp: Quantumania]]''. After the character's death, his consciousness was going to live on through the [[ants]], this idea was later scrapped.<ref>[https://geektyrant.com/news/hank-pym-was-almost-killed-off-in-ant-man-and-the-wasp-quantumania Hank Pym Was Almost Killed Off in ANT-MAN 3 But Would've Still Existed in a Bizarre Way]</ref>
*[[Michael Runyard]] and [[Martin Vose]] were stunt doubles for [[Michael Douglas]] in the role of Hank Pym.

